Jon:
&lt;snip&gt;
Wouldn&#39;t this be what you would want if you just want to cause a resource to
exist?


   1. PUT /foo (empty body)
   2. GET /foo -&gt; 204 No Content

&lt;/snip&gt;

I suppose that could be done. I&#39;ve not had a need to do this in the past;
usually some body data is sent by clients when creating a resources on
servers I work with.

Are you using this pattern now?

